caption: Nice statue in front of the Army museum.
Marie Emile Fayolle was a marshal of French army. He came back from his retirement to support his country in first world war.
Imposing statue of Marie Émile Fayolle (Le Puy-en-Velay, May 14, 1852. Paris, August 27, 1928) Marshal of France who stood out with the rank of general during the First World War.
Marie Émile Fayolle (1852-1928). Major general, influential during the First World War, commanded French forces in Italy (1917), to reinforce the Italian front after the failure of "Camporetto".
